        itineraire: "The route follows the A64 for its entire length from Toulouse to Pau. After leaving the Toulouse suburbs, the motorway crosses the Comminges with its green rolling hills and Gascon farms. You pass Saint-Gaudens, then Lannemezan on its windy plateau. The landscape gradually evolves: Gers hills give way to the first Pyrenean foothills. After Tarbes, the motorway continues westward with the Pyrenees now in full view, magnificently snow-capped in winter. Arrival in Pau is via the Pau Centre exit, and the descent towards the Gave de Pau river offers a spectacular view of the castle and the Boulevard des Pyrénées. A64 tolls total approximately €17. The journey takes 2h normally and can reach 2h35 during rush hours or in rainy weather (the A64 is highly exposed to wind and rain between Lannemezan and Tarbes).",
